<div class="container">
    <h2>Resources for Climate Advocacy</h2>
    <p>Here are some organizations and institutions you can reach out to for more information, help, and advocacy:</p>
    
    <ul>
        <li>
            <a href="https://www.canada.ca/en/services/environment/weather.html" target="_blank">Government of Canada - Environment and Climate Change</a>
            <p>The Government of Canada's official site provides information on climate change policies, environmental services, and ways citizens can take action to reduce their environmental impact.</p>
        </li>

        <li>
            <a href="https://climate.nasa.gov/" target="_blank">NASA Climate Change: Vital Signs of the Planet</a>
            <p>This NASA portal offers up-to-date data on climate change indicators, including global temperature, carbon dioxide levels, and sea level rise. It provides detailed reports, articles, and visualizations to help understand the impact of climate change on Earth.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <a href="https://earthdata.nasa.gov/" target="_blank">NASA EarthData</a>
            <p>EarthData provides access to satellite data on climate, oceans, land, atmosphere, and more. It offers tools and resources for understanding and analyzing Earth system data collected by NASA's Earth Observing System.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <a href="https://climate.nasa.gov/resources/education/" target="_blank">NASA Climate Change Education Resources</a>
            <p>This section of NASA's Climate Change portal provides educational materials for teachers, students, and the public, focusing on climate science, the impact of climate change, and what can be done to mitigate it.</p>
        </li>
        
        <li>
            <a href="https://science.nasa.gov/earth-science/oceanography/living-ocean" target="_blank">NASA Oceanography: Living Ocean</a>
            <p>This NASA program focuses on the relationship between the Earth's oceans and climate change. It provides valuable insights into how oceans absorb heat and carbon, helping to regulate the planet’s climate.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <a href="https://climate.nasa.gov/resources/global-warming-vs-climate-change/" target="_blank">Global Warming vs. Climate Change – NASA</a>
            <p>This page helps to clarify the difference between global warming and climate change, providing scientific explanations and evidence of how these processes affect Earth's ecosystems and populations.</p>
        </li>

        <li>
            <a href="https://www.wri.org/" target="_blank">World Resources Institute</a>
            <p>World Resources Institute focuses on climate, energy, and sustainability research and solutions. It provides tools, data, and research to address global climate challenges.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <a href="https://www.nrdc.org/" target="_blank">Natural Resources Defense Council</a>
            <p>The NRDC works to safeguard the earth by focusing on clean energy, global warming, and policies that protect natural resources and communities from environmental threats.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <a href="https://www.greenpeace.org/" target="_blank">Greenpeace</a>
            <p>Greenpeace is an independent global campaigning organization that works to protect the environment and promote peace by tackling issues such as climate change, deforestation, and pollution.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <a href="https://www.worldwildlife.org/" target="_blank">World Wildlife Fund</a>
            <p>WWF is dedicated to wildlife conservation and endangered species protection, with a focus on climate resilience, sustainable practices, and habitat preservation.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <a href="https://earth.gov/ghgcenter/stories" target="_blank">U.S. GHG Center Stories</a>
            <p>The U.S. GHG Center provides data and stories about greenhouse gas emissions reduction efforts, research, and policies that address the challenges of climate change.</p>
        </li>

        
    </ul>

    <h3>Advocacy Tips</h3>
    <p>Here are some ways you can advocate for climate action:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Engage with your community by participating in local environmental events.</li>
        <li>Reach out to local representatives to express your concerns about climate change.</li>
        <li>Share information and educate others about climate issues.</li>
    </ul>
</div>
